# ESLint & Code Quality

## Zero Warnings Policy

- **Leave zero lint warnings or errors** after any change
- Run `pnpm lint` after edits and fix all reported issues
- Do not introduce new warnings "for later" — fix them immediately

## Unused Code

- **Remove unused imports** — delete imports that are not referenced
- **Remove unused variables** — delete or use variables; prefix with `_` only when required by a callback signature (e.g. `_issueId`)
- **Remove unused type imports** — use `type` imports only when the type is used

## React Hooks Dependencies

- **Include all dependencies** in `useEffect`, `useMemo`, `useCallback` dependency arrays
- If a value changes every render, wrap it in `useMemo` or `useCallback` first
- Use `eslint-disable-next-line react-hooks/exhaustive-deps` only when adding a dep would cause infinite loops — add a brief comment explaining why

## Before Finishing

After making changes, run:
1. `pnpm typecheck` — must pass
2. `pnpm lint` — must pass with zero warnings
